File: South Africa's Miss Universe, Zozibini Tunzi, is spreading positivity and support, remotely of course. NEW YORK - Miss Universe is supposed to be travelling the world, pushing various causes. This has been made impossible by the coronavirus pandemic. IN PICTURES: Zozibini Tunzi's Miss Universe journey South Africa's Miss Universe, Zozibini Tunzi, is not letting this stop her. She's launched a hashtag, #UniverseUnited on social media to provide a platform for people to share how they're keeping entertained at home. "For now stay safe, stay sane. Do what needs to be done to flatten the curve. Sending all my love and light," Tunzi said on her Twitter page. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs